 and weigh in meat. Add Worcestershire sauce, cloves, 1 tsp salt and pepper. Stir together and set aside."},{"content":"Place onions, garlic and olive oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and sauté <b>2 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved meat, carrots, celery and parsnips then cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add flour, tomato purée, stock cube and water then cook <b>30 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Add peas, sweetcorn and mushrooms then cook <b>20 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b> until beef is tender."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Transfer stew into 6 serving bowls. Place mashed potatoes in an icing bag with a 5 cm cut base (without nozzle). Pipe ghost shapes into stew and garnish each ghost with 2 reserved peas for eyes. Serve immediately."}],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 30m","6 portions"]}